  "texts": [
    "When identifying the spot on a leaf that's been damaged, morphological traits prove more effective than others (Yao et al., 2009; Khirade and Patil, 2015).",
    "Color features like color moments and Gabor texture are frequently used.",
    "Several methods are available for obtaining these characteristics, such as the color histogram (Sugimura et al., 2015), the color correlogram (Huang et al., 1997), the color R moment (Rahhal et al., 2016), and others.",
    "Contrast, homogeneity, variance, and entropy are all potential additions to the texture.",
    "In the context of plant disease identification problems, it has been discovered that texture feature usage yields more favorable outcomes (Kaur et al, 2019)."
  ],
